<strong>Author's Notes:</strong>
This piece was one of my many attempts at tackling the contrapuntal form. I don't know that I am entirely satisfied with the result, but I am rarely if ever satisfied with such creatively freeing constraints as these. 

For the uninitiated, the contrapuntal poem is one formed from multiple other poems in such a way that each component poem stands alone, not just the combined result. In the case of "you should know," the poem can be read down the right side, down the left side, or from left to right, and the two component poems are so drastically dissimilar that the combination captures a uniquely hanting dichotomy of perspective.